1) cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning object representations from monocular videos, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2) cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper demonstrates the usefulness of the proposed approach in robotics settings. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a self-supervised approach for learning representations using contrastive learning. 
4) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with learning representations of objects, which is a fundamental problem in AI. 
5) cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of natural language to describe the objects in the videos.
